  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">An overview of the ATLAS liquid-argon calorimeter system is provided, along with a discussion of its operation and performance during the first year of LHC running. Upgrade planning related to the proposed high-luminosity upgrade of the LHC is also discussed, with an emphasis on the forward part of the calorimeter where the effects of the higher luminosity can seriously degrade the calorimeter performance.</subfield>
